00:30:03.630 --> 00:30:09.180 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: But the part we bring
to the party is in the science.

00:30:09.180 --> 00:30:10.030 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:30:10.030 --> 00:30:11.613 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: We have
developed technology

00:30:11.613 --> 00:30:13.060 align:middle line:84%
at the Institute
of HeartMath that

00:30:13.060 --> 00:30:16.560 align:middle line:84%
measures subtle changes in
the Earth's energetic fields.

00:30:16.560 --> 00:30:19.150 align:middle line:84%
The Earth produces
energetic fields itself.

00:30:19.150 --> 00:30:20.850 align:middle line:84%
Part of the Earth
is a living system

00:30:20.850 --> 00:30:22.650 align:middle line:90%
are these energetic fields.

00:30:22.650 --> 00:30:23.720 align:middle line:90%
There are two primarily.

00:30:23.720 --> 00:30:25.530 align:middle line:84%
One's called the
geomagnetic field,

00:30:25.530 --> 00:30:27.020 align:middle line:84%
most people are
familiar with that.

00:30:27.020 --> 00:30:29.754 align:middle line:84%
That's what a compass is picking
up is the geomagnetic field.

00:30:29.754 --> 00:30:30.920 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, interesting, OK.

00:30:30.920 --> 00:30:32.050 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: It's created
by the iron core

00:30:32.050 --> 00:30:34.720 align:middle line:84%
spinning in the center of
the Earth, creating a field,

00:30:34.720 --> 00:30:36.490 align:middle line:90%
energy around the Earth.

00:30:36.490 --> 00:30:38.190 align:middle line:90%
The other's call the ionosphere.

00:30:38.190 --> 00:30:42.014 align:middle line:84%
And it's a field less dense
than the geomagnetic field, that

00:30:42.014 --> 00:30:43.430 align:middle line:84%
operates just above
the atmosphere

00:30:43.430 --> 00:30:44.980 align:middle line:90%
and goes up into space.

00:30:44.980 --> 00:30:48.890 align:middle line:84%
This is the last field
we have-- the last part

00:30:48.890 --> 00:30:50.730 align:middle line:84%
of the Earth is an
energetic system.

00:30:50.730 --> 00:30:54.940 align:middle line:84%
These fields are protective
layers around our planet.

00:30:54.940 --> 00:30:57.620 align:middle line:84%
Without the fields, there
would be no life here.

00:30:57.620 --> 00:30:59.940 align:middle line:84%
And so they're a part
of what protects us

00:30:59.940 --> 00:31:02.765 align:middle line:84%
from incoming solar
radiation, the cosmic rays,

00:31:02.765 --> 00:31:04.890 align:middle line:84%
and all these different
things that would killed us

00:31:04.890 --> 00:31:06.740 align:middle line:90%
if we didn't have these fields.

00:31:06.740 --> 00:31:10.024 align:middle line:90%
So we know these fields exist.

00:31:10.024 --> 00:31:11.690 align:middle line:84%
A lot of research has
been done already,

00:31:11.690 --> 00:31:13.670 align:middle line:84%
and more is being
done now, showing

00:31:13.670 --> 00:31:15.372 align:middle line:84%
that when these fields
begin to change--

00:31:15.372 --> 00:31:17.080 align:middle line:84%
and they change all
the time, they always

00:31:17.080 --> 00:31:20.830 align:middle line:84%
fluctuate-- that
there is impact on us.

00:31:20.830 --> 00:31:24.690 align:middle line:84%
Things like increases in
crime rates, health issues,

00:31:24.690 --> 00:31:27.290 align:middle line:84%
terrorism, even wars
have been linked

00:31:27.290 --> 00:31:29.800 align:middle line:84%
to changes in these
cycles-- solar cycles

00:31:29.800 --> 00:31:31.285 align:middle line:90%
that impact these fields.

00:31:31.285 --> 00:31:32.910 align:middle line:84%
So we know that
there's a relationship,

00:31:32.910 --> 00:31:34.200 align:middle line:90%
that the field's impacting us.

00:31:34.200 --> 00:31:36.280 align:middle line:90%
So we know it's coming this way.

00:31:36.280 --> 00:31:38.080 align:middle line:84%
So the hypothesis
that we're testing--

00:31:38.080 --> 00:31:39.663 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Wait, wait,
can you tell ahead

00:31:39.663 --> 00:31:42.660 align:middle line:84%
of time that those
fields are shifting

00:31:42.660 --> 00:31:45.455 align:middle line:84%
and that we will have
higher crime rates?

00:31:45.455 --> 00:31:47.080 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: In a way
you can, because you

00:31:47.080 --> 00:31:49.000 align:middle line:84%
can look at the solar
activity, for example,

00:31:49.000 --> 00:31:50.833 align:middle line:84%
and know that there's
going to be an impact,

00:31:50.833 --> 00:31:52.890 align:middle line:84%
because there's been a
solar flare, et cetera.

00:31:52.890 --> 00:31:53.370 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:31:53.370 --> 00:31:54.860 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: You don't know what
effect it's going to have

00:31:54.860 --> 00:31:55.564 align:middle line:90%
necessarily.

00:31:55.564 --> 00:31:57.980 align:middle line:84%
You have to look sort of back
through the rear view mirror

00:31:57.980 --> 00:31:59.620 align:middle line:84%
to see what happened
and then correlate

00:31:59.620 --> 00:32:00.953 align:middle line:90%
those things to build a picture.

00:32:00.953 --> 00:32:02.790 align:middle line:84%
But, yeah, the
solar cycles, if you

00:32:02.790 --> 00:32:04.380 align:middle line:84%
look at the data
on the solar cycles

00:32:04.380 --> 00:32:07.550 align:middle line:84%
and how they go through these
13-year solar cycle periods,

00:32:07.550 --> 00:32:08.940 align:middle line:84%
and you see that
they're attached

00:32:08.940 --> 00:32:11.360 align:middle line:84%
to certain types
of events, you can

00:32:11.360 --> 00:32:15.262 align:middle line:84%
begin to see the possibility
those events would occur again.

00:32:15.262 --> 00:32:18.160 align:middle line:84%
I'm of the belief that you can
actually offset some of that,

00:32:18.160 --> 00:32:20.845 align:middle line:84%
you can change it, but you can
see that there are potentially

00:32:20.845 --> 00:32:24.240 align:middle line:84%
events that would occur relative
to the cycles of the past.

00:32:24.240 --> 00:32:27.080 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So do they
affect electronics?

00:32:27.080 --> 00:32:29.262 align:middle line:90%
Do they affect human beings?

00:32:29.262 --> 00:32:29.970 align:middle line:90%
All of the above?

00:32:29.970 --> 00:32:30.250 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTIN: All of it.

00:32:30.250 --> 00:32:30.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Got it.

00:32:30.560 --> 00:32:30.890 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:32:30.890 --> 00:32:31.120 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTIN: All if it.

00:32:31.120 --> 00:32:31.720 align:middle line:90%
They really do.

00:32:31.720 --> 00:32:32.770 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And so you can
look at the cycles?

00:32:32.770 --> 00:32:33.140 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:32:33.140 --> 00:32:33.870 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTIN: Sure.

00:32:33.870 --> 00:32:37.920 align:middle line:84%
So the hypotheses we have
is that mass human emotion,

00:32:37.920 --> 00:32:41.250 align:middle line:84%
whether that's positive
emotion or negative emotion,

00:32:41.250 --> 00:32:44.422 align:middle line:84%
is also having an
impact on the fields.

00:32:44.422 --> 00:32:45.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it's in
reverse as well?

00:32:45.880 --> 00:32:46.830 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTIN: In reverse.

00:32:46.830 --> 00:32:49.079 align:middle line:84%
The reason to believe that
is if they're affecting us,

00:32:49.079 --> 00:32:51.554 align:middle line:84%
why would we not have a
relationship to affect them?

00:32:51.554 --> 00:32:52.970 align:middle line:84%
The other thing
that's interesting

00:32:52.970 --> 00:32:54.860 align:middle line:84%
is that some of the
frequencies produced

00:32:54.860 --> 00:32:59.070 align:middle line:84%
by the-- that are
found in the ionosphere

00:32:59.070 --> 00:33:00.960 align:middle line:84%
are exactly the same
frequencies found

00:33:00.960 --> 00:33:02.300 align:middle line:90%
in the human heart and brain.

00:33:02.300 --> 00:33:02.720 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

00:33:02.720 --> 00:33:04.928 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: So we know there's
an energetic alignment--

00:33:04.928 --> 00:33:06.157 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: As above, so below.

00:33:06.157 --> 00:33:07.740 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: --alignment
between the two.

00:33:07.740 --> 00:33:11.140 align:middle line:84%
So the hypothesis is is when
we have large numbers of people

00:33:11.140 --> 00:33:13.520 align:middle line:84%
feeling something similar,
that that sends out

00:33:13.520 --> 00:33:17.690 align:middle line:84%
enough energy that impacts these
fields that can be measured.

00:33:17.690 --> 00:33:22.390 align:middle line:84%
So for instance, let's
say there's a major event.

00:33:22.390 --> 00:33:23.840 align:middle line:90%
It could be something positive.

00:33:23.840 --> 00:33:26.670 align:middle line:84%
It could be the opening of an
Olympics or something, possibly

00:33:26.670 --> 00:33:27.950 align:middle line:90%
that could be detected.

00:33:27.950 --> 00:33:30.450 align:middle line:84%
Or let's say that there's
a major disaster--

00:33:30.450 --> 00:33:31.554 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Space shuttle.

00:33:31.554 --> 00:33:32.970 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: And
people are feeling--

00:33:32.970 --> 00:33:35.830 align:middle line:84%
all over the world are feeling
a sense of angst and upset,

00:33:35.830 --> 00:33:38.650 align:middle line:84%
and all that, that
could be measured.

00:33:38.650 --> 00:33:41.360 align:middle line:84%
And so the goal of
the project in a sense

00:33:41.360 --> 00:33:42.840 align:middle line:84%
from a scientific
perspective would

00:33:42.840 --> 00:33:45.930 align:middle line:84%
be to show that our thoughts,
our feelings, our emotions,

00:33:45.930 --> 00:33:49.070 align:middle line:84%
our prayers, our meditations,
our intentions-- all

00:33:49.070 --> 00:33:52.200 align:middle line:84%
these things that we do and
have done for thousands of years

00:33:52.200 --> 00:33:55.840 align:middle line:84%
are putting out a collective
energy that is measurable,

00:33:55.840 --> 00:33:58.030 align:middle line:84%
that is impacting
and contributing

00:33:58.030 --> 00:34:01.140 align:middle line:84%
to what goes on in the Earth
as a living system, that there

00:34:01.140 --> 00:34:03.007 align:middle line:84%
is that direct
connection to that.

00:34:03.007 --> 00:34:04.590 align:middle line:84%
Ultimately, and this
is down the road,

00:34:04.590 --> 00:34:08.929 align:middle line:84%
the science has
to be done right.

00:34:08.929 --> 00:34:12.370 align:middle line:84%
Ultimately, I'd like to be
able to say we can bring people

00:34:12.370 --> 00:34:15.380 align:middle line:84%
together in the coherent state,
a large number of people,

00:34:15.380 --> 00:34:18.310 align:middle line:84%
maybe 350,000 is an
estimate of what we need,

00:34:18.310 --> 00:34:22.690 align:middle line:84%
to be operating in another
level of coherence,

00:34:22.690 --> 00:34:25.900 align:middle line:84%
putting out care and intention
toward something that

00:34:25.900 --> 00:34:28.440 align:middle line:84%
could then be measured in
the fields, that could then

00:34:28.440 --> 00:34:30.409 align:middle line:84%
be correlated with
something positive that

00:34:30.409 --> 00:34:31.868 align:middle line:90%
occurred in society.

00:34:31.868 --> 00:34:33.409 align:middle line:84%
Now, there's a lot
of experimentation

00:34:33.409 --> 00:34:35.290 align:middle line:90%
to get that job done.

00:34:35.290 --> 00:34:36.840 align:middle line:84%
Right now we have,
for example, we

00:34:36.840 --> 00:34:39.190 align:middle line:84%
have these-- we have
monitoring sites.

00:34:39.190 --> 00:34:41.570 align:middle line:84%
We have one in
northern California.

00:34:41.570 --> 00:34:44.710 align:middle line:84%
We have one in the
United Kingdom.

00:34:44.710 --> 00:34:46.679 align:middle line:90%
We have one in Saudi Arabia.

00:34:46.679 --> 00:34:48.639 align:middle line:84%
There'll be two more
coming very, very soon,

00:34:48.639 --> 00:34:51.810 align:middle line:84%
one in northern Canada
and one in New Zealand.

00:34:51.810 --> 00:34:54.110 align:middle line:90%
And ultimately, we'll have 12.

00:34:54.110 --> 00:34:55.997 align:middle line:84%
Scientists are
looking at data now.

00:34:55.997 --> 00:34:58.330 align:middle line:84%
They're trying to make sense
out of what they're seeing.

00:34:58.330 --> 00:35:00.540 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot of filtering
that has to be done.

00:35:00.540 --> 00:35:02.720 align:middle line:84%
A lot of research to
do this in a way that

00:35:02.720 --> 00:35:07.144 align:middle line:90%
can be definitive and empirical.

00:35:07.144 --> 00:35:09.310 align:middle line:84%
So the research will
contribute to the understanding

00:35:09.310 --> 00:35:13.030 align:middle line:84%
of our spiritual nature and
our collective consciousness.

00:35:13.030 --> 00:35:15.810 align:middle line:84%
It will also contribute to
the academic understanding

00:35:15.810 --> 00:35:17.230 align:middle line:90%
of the fields themselves.

00:35:17.230 --> 00:35:19.750 align:middle line:84%
So it's both above
and below again,

00:35:19.750 --> 00:35:21.630 align:middle line:84%
and the balance that,
I think, HeartMath

00:35:21.630 --> 00:35:23.330 align:middle line:90%
