00:40:12.160 --> 00:40:13.140 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Oh,
absolutely, absolutely.

00:40:13.140 --> 00:40:13.950 align:middle line:90%
OK, we're going to do that.

00:40:13.950 --> 00:40:14.910 align:middle line:84%
We're going to
take a quick break.

00:40:14.910 --> 00:40:15.880 align:middle line:84%
And when we come
back, we're going

00:40:15.880 --> 00:40:17.390 align:middle line:84%
to set up the
technology here so we

00:40:17.390 --> 00:40:18.990 align:middle line:84%
can have a
demonstration of this.

00:40:18.990 --> 00:40:22.470 align:middle line:84%
All right, we'll be right
back with Howard Martin.

00:40:22.470 --> 00:40:23.200 align:middle line:90%
Hi, welcome back.

00:40:23.200 --> 00:40:25.730 align:middle line:84%
I'm Lisa Garr, and my guest
is Howard Martin, the vice

00:40:25.730 --> 00:40:27.980 align:middle line:84%
president-- the executive
vice president of HeartMath.

00:40:27.980 --> 00:40:29.355 align:middle line:84%
Before the break,
we were talking

00:40:29.355 --> 00:40:32.740 align:middle line:84%
about how the heart sends
information to the brain.

00:40:32.740 --> 00:40:34.944 align:middle line:84%
But how does the heart
receive information?

00:40:34.944 --> 00:40:36.360 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: Well,
we definitely have

00:40:36.360 --> 00:40:38.845 align:middle line:84%
done one study that may
show that the heart is also

00:40:38.845 --> 00:40:40.185 align:middle line:90%
a receptor of information.

00:40:40.185 --> 00:40:42.643 align:middle line:84%
Sure it gets information from
the brain, controlling timing

00:40:42.643 --> 00:40:45.840 align:middle line:84%
of the heart beat, but I'm
talking about information

00:40:45.840 --> 00:40:49.275 align:middle line:84%
that applies to what we
call heart intelligence.

00:40:49.275 --> 00:40:52.090 align:middle line:84%
It's called the intuition study,
the physiology of intuition.

00:40:52.090 --> 00:40:52.860 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, nice.

00:40:52.860 --> 00:40:54.102 align:middle line:90%
We could do-- perfect.

00:40:54.102 --> 00:40:56.560 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: What our scientists
at the Institute of HeartMath

00:40:56.560 --> 00:40:58.535 align:middle line:84%
wanted to do is to
look at was there

00:40:58.535 --> 00:41:01.330 align:middle line:84%
a way to begin to
decode what happens

00:41:01.330 --> 00:41:02.891 align:middle line:90%
in the intuitive process.

00:41:02.891 --> 00:41:05.390 align:middle line:84%
So they did a study where they
had a group of test subjects,

00:41:05.390 --> 00:41:08.160 align:middle line:84%
and they were monitoring all
kinds of things on their body--

00:41:08.160 --> 00:41:11.460 align:middle line:84%
brainwave activity, skin
response, heart activity-- lots

00:41:11.460 --> 00:41:14.160 align:middle line:84%
of things being monitored
all at the same time.

00:41:14.160 --> 00:41:16.275 align:middle line:84%
Test subjects were set
in front of a computer.

00:41:16.275 --> 00:41:17.914 align:middle line:90%
They would push a button.

00:41:17.914 --> 00:41:19.580 align:middle line:84%
Indeterminate amount
of time would go on

00:41:19.580 --> 00:41:20.914 align:middle line:90%
and then a picture would emerge.

00:41:20.914 --> 00:41:22.455 align:middle line:84%
And they would push
the button again,

00:41:22.455 --> 00:41:24.060 align:middle line:84%
and another picture
would emerge.

00:41:24.060 --> 00:41:26.690 align:middle line:84%
Pictures were either
very horrific,

00:41:26.690 --> 00:41:28.459 align:middle line:84%
like very things that
are very upsetting--

00:41:28.459 --> 00:41:29.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Disturbing?

00:41:29.250 --> 00:41:30.140 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTIN: Disturbing pictures.

00:41:30.140 --> 00:41:32.000 align:middle line:84%
Or there would be very
beautiful pictures.

00:41:32.000 --> 00:41:32.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:41:32.500 --> 00:41:34.500 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: And so they
just would hit the button,

00:41:34.500 --> 00:41:35.710 align:middle line:84%
sit there, and wait
for the picture.

00:41:35.710 --> 00:41:37.460 align:middle line:84%
And the picture would
emerge, and all this data

00:41:37.460 --> 00:41:38.410 align:middle line:90%
was being collected.

00:41:38.410 --> 00:41:39.490 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The person was
hitting the button?

00:41:39.490 --> 00:41:39.780 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTIN: Yeah.

00:41:39.780 --> 00:41:40.310 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:41:40.310 --> 00:41:41.820 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: So then,
the data began

00:41:41.820 --> 00:41:43.460 align:middle line:90%
to be analyzed from this study.

00:41:43.460 --> 00:41:46.410 align:middle line:84%
And what they found was was,
oh, my gosh, look at this.

00:41:46.410 --> 00:41:48.660 align:middle line:84%
In many cases, the
body is responding

00:41:48.660 --> 00:41:51.490 align:middle line:84%
to the upcoming
picture about 6 seconds

00:41:51.490 --> 00:41:54.560 align:middle line:84%
before the picture
actually shows up.

00:41:54.560 --> 00:41:57.107 align:middle line:84%
And they thought
this was really--

00:41:57.107 --> 00:41:58.190 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting, yeah.

00:41:58.190 --> 00:41:59.020 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: --interesting
what's happening here,

00:41:59.020 --> 00:42:01.307 align:middle line:84%
this picture's-- is
not even there yet,

00:42:01.307 --> 00:42:03.640 align:middle line:84%
but the body's doing what it
would do if the picture was

00:42:03.640 --> 00:42:03.820 align:middle line:90%
there.

00:42:03.820 --> 00:42:04.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So it's intuiting?

00:42:04.970 --> 00:42:06.760 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: Intuiting
the upcoming picture.

00:42:06.760 --> 00:42:08.590 align:middle line:84%
Now where it got
more intriguing is

00:42:08.590 --> 00:42:13.300 align:middle line:84%
as they began to decode and
decode this information more--

00:42:13.300 --> 00:42:14.680 align:middle line:84%
in a more refined
way, they found

00:42:14.680 --> 00:42:18.260 align:middle line:84%
that the first physiological
responder to the picture that

00:42:18.260 --> 00:42:20.655 align:middle line:90%
wasn't there was the heart.

00:42:20.655 --> 00:42:22.280 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Oh, they
could measure it, wow.

00:42:22.280 --> 00:42:23.687 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: 6 seconds
out the heart

00:42:23.687 --> 00:42:26.270 align:middle line:84%
began to do what it would do if
the picture was on the screen.

00:42:26.270 --> 00:42:29.520 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Could it tell if it was
in a love or if it was in fear,

00:42:29.520 --> 00:42:30.840 align:middle line:90%
or was it just a spike?

00:42:30.840 --> 00:42:33.400 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: No, it was like being
able to tell whether it was

00:42:33.400 --> 00:42:36.234 align:middle line:84%
responding to a horrific
picture or a beautiful picture,

00:42:36.234 --> 00:42:37.650 align:middle line:84%
it was like it was
doing all that.

00:42:37.650 --> 00:42:39.510 align:middle line:84%
The brain was the
second responder.

00:42:39.510 --> 00:42:41.300 align:middle line:84%
And then the two began
to work together,

00:42:41.300 --> 00:42:43.640 align:middle line:84%
they couple together
about a second

00:42:43.640 --> 00:42:45.650 align:middle line:84%
before the picture
actually emerged.

00:42:45.650 --> 00:42:48.417 align:middle line:84%
So what this shows is
that the possibility

00:42:48.417 --> 00:42:50.250 align:middle line:84%
that the heart is a
receptor of information.

00:42:50.250 --> 00:42:52.560 align:middle line:84%
It's receiving information
from the outside.

00:42:52.560 --> 00:42:55.630 align:middle line:84%
It's picking up information
from the field, so to speak,

00:42:55.630 --> 00:42:57.800 align:middle line:84%
that we all live in--
this information field.

00:42:57.800 --> 00:43:01.180 align:middle line:84%
And what the researchers said
is it appears as if-- you know,

00:43:01.180 --> 00:43:03.810 align:middle line:84%
if something is significant,
emotionally significant,

00:43:03.810 --> 00:43:07.150 align:middle line:84%
it could be precipitating a
physiological response that

00:43:07.150 --> 00:43:11.230 align:middle line:84%
would be congruent with
the upcoming event.

00:43:11.230 --> 00:43:15.940 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So if you have a
feeling about a car accident

00:43:15.940 --> 00:43:18.440 align:middle line:84%
and you delay
yourself in leaving,

00:43:18.440 --> 00:43:20.580 align:middle line:84%
you'll never really see
the evidence of that,

00:43:20.580 --> 00:43:22.950 align:middle line:84%
but that could very
well be your intuition

00:43:22.950 --> 00:43:24.704 align:middle line:84%
at work being
amazingly accurate.

00:43:24.704 --> 00:43:27.120 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: Finding future events,
looking at future events.

00:43:27.120 --> 00:43:30.090 align:middle line:84%
And we've had these experiences
in our lives, many people have.

00:43:30.090 --> 00:43:33.530 align:middle line:84%
I certainly have to where
certain decisions that I made

00:43:33.530 --> 00:43:35.890 align:middle line:84%
turned out to be, wow, how
did I make that choice?

00:43:35.890 --> 00:43:38.840 align:middle line:84%
And that was a very
intelligent thing to do.

00:43:38.840 --> 00:43:40.820 align:middle line:84%
In talking to the
scientists, they said,

00:43:40.820 --> 00:43:44.290 align:middle line:84%
look, it appears as if we do
have intelligences within us,

00:43:44.290 --> 00:43:46.540 align:middle line:84%
intelligence capacities
that are there all the time.

00:43:46.540 --> 00:43:49.250 align:middle line:84%
That our body, in this case, may
be scanning for future events

00:43:49.250 --> 00:43:50.650 align:middle line:84%
all the time, that
may be reading

00:43:50.650 --> 00:43:54.360 align:middle line:84%
the field, beyond time
and space into the future.

00:43:54.360 --> 00:43:56.230 align:middle line:84%
And that these are
the kinds of things

00:43:56.230 --> 00:43:58.894 align:middle line:84%
that will emerge more as
we evolve as human beings.

00:43:58.894 --> 00:44:00.560 align:middle line:84%
This type of intelligence
will come more

00:44:00.560 --> 00:44:02.580 align:middle line:84%
to the forefront of
what's normal for us.

00:44:02.580 --> 00:44:05.010 align:middle line:84%
Right now it's phenomenalistic,
it's not understood,

00:44:05.010 --> 00:44:06.430 align:middle line:90%
it feels bizarre.

00:44:06.430 --> 00:44:09.456 align:middle line:84%
But in the future, as we unfold
ourselves as human beings,

00:44:09.456 --> 00:44:10.830 align:middle line:84%
there's lots of
new ways in which

00:44:10.830 --> 00:44:12.694 align:middle line:84%
we'll be able to
perceive things.

00:44:12.694 --> 00:44:14.360 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Let me ask
you, just knowing all

00:44:14.360 --> 00:44:17.520 align:middle line:84%
that you know about the heart
and about the human resonance

00:44:17.520 --> 00:44:20.180 align:middle line:84%
field, and about intuition,
do you live your life any

00:44:20.180 --> 00:44:24.095 align:middle line:84%
differently now than you
did, say, 20-30 years ago?

00:44:24.095 --> 00:44:24.970 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTIN: Absolutely.

00:44:24.970 --> 00:44:26.345 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Before
you knew all this?

00:44:26.345 --> 00:44:28.102 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTIN: Listen, come on, yeah.

00:44:28.102 --> 00:44:29.810 align:middle line:84%
I don't know where I
would be if I hadn't

00:44:29.810 --> 00:44:34.830 align:middle line:84%
